nguage=EN>Sarmaldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/27/01 6:55:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   NPC special attacks</span><hr size=1> Hello all,<br>
<br>
Could someone with more EQ savvy than me explain all the NPC special attacks suck as enrage, rampage, etc. I think there are four, but Im not sure. I've looked around and havent seen much on the internet sites so I thought I would try here. Multiple answers from multiple posters would be useful, since I am not the only one who isnt exactly sure. Enrage is pretty obvious, but the others???? I think there is an AE attack, and one that gives the NPC 'buffs' for a brief time, but I hear alot of different things so I thought I might bring it here to get more opinions.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ureegeraxehaft.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reeger Axehaft</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/27/01 10:42:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NPC special attacks</span><hr size=1> Okay, not sure about Rampage, so speculating could be incorrect.  Enraged seems to be when the mob hits about 10% life it ripostes every attack if you are considered in melee range or sight.  You can still hit it from some side angles and definetly from the back.  If I am in front of the offending MoB, I usually stop attacking and play rogue, get behind, then commence to beating the piss out of it.   Enraged only lasts like 15 seconds or around there. <p>Reeger Axehaft <BR>
53rd Level Warrior <BR>
"Let me Axe you a question!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/27/01 12:01:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NPC special attacks</span><hr size=1> The best guess or explanation for Rampage that I have heard is that it lets the mob hit the top 3 or so people on his hate list no matter where they are if they're in melee range.<br>
<br>
There is also Flurry, which I believe is like a string of attacks that will land no matter what.   <p>~Tunare's Enforcer~<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4080">Aeril Droigheann</a>, 59 Preserver<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4050">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br>
Aerul Cuinnsear, 43 Rogue<br>
Undaunted, Xegony<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uclaeborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Claeborn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hem2.passagen.se/~tkarman/tiny.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 1:21:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NPC special attacks</span><hr size=1> From my encounters I gather that these are the special attacks -<br>
<br>
Rampage = AE attack that hits the top 3-5 people on the hate list of the mob (Not sure about the amount of targets)<br>
Enrage = Auto-ripostes all attacks from the front<br>
Flurry = Up to 6 attacks that all land on target if the first attack lands<br>
<br>
Cheerio <p><center><a href="http://hem.passagen.se/tkarman/claeborn/index.htm" target="_blank"><img src="http://hem.passagen.se/tkarman/sigval.jpg" border="0"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=okiro>Okiro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 2:38:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NPC special attacks</span><hr size=1> Seen screen shots of FOH facing the Avatar of War. Flurry seems to be like a combo of attacks, around 6 to 9 at a time.  Some hit, some miss, I think it just means he gets more than a chance to double attack, dual wield (4 hits most) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umintzyfresch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mintzy Fresch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/01 12:37:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/uryvichk/mintzy.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NPC special attacks</span><hr size=1> Does Rampage have a melee radius? &quot;Hits the top 3 people on the hate list&quot; seems kinda vague, what if #3 is a ways away?<br>
<br>
-Mintzy Fresch,<br>
Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umyztic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/01 11:46:39 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: NPC special attacks</span><hr size=1> Enrage = just like our 56th riposte disc, mobs enrage around 10% life and it lasts about 10 sec<br>
<br>
Flurry = The Double Attack, so if mob was quad attacking and kicking, it will attack 8 times and kick twice<br>
<br>
Rampage = mob will hit 3-5 players in top of hate list, they don't have to be in melee range, if mob quads, it will quad all those unlucky peeps<br>
<br>
NOW... a sidenote, I haven't EVER gotten any damage from rampage. Never. I've been main tanking Dain for example, and on rampage rounds other tanks got damage but me and buddy ogre. There is long discussions going on if ogres are immune to rampage or not, I am one who says we are. I suppose rampage is coded to be an stun-type melee attack, and umm... ogres are immune to frontal stuns.<br>
<br>
